  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My father was a, a kind of a very bookish man, in a way.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was-- he had a huge library of rabbinical books and was what, in [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the world knows from Chaim Nahman Bialik's famous poem, he was a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He was a-- he could be lost for days and nights in his books.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He was much sought after, particularly [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] as an expert in halachah, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Very frequently [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] called in by rabbinic courts to be an arbitrator or whatever, a dayan, or what they call a [INAUDIBLE], which, really, is kind of a counsel comme defense lawyer or something like that.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Curiously enough, although he was a, a star student of a very famous rabbi, Hasidic rabbi, the [?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Munkacser ?] Rebbe, who was quite an institution himself, he was not really a Hasid in what came to be known in the philosophical sense-- and certainly what it came to be known in the literature of Hasidism, late Hasidism-- he was not-- he was too rational and too involved in the-- in the rationale or, or rational approach of the Talmud and rabbinic literature.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he was not given to this-- to the mysticism [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which Hasidism absorbed and, and propagated.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- even his attire sort of separated him from, from Hasidism, although in his observance, he was as strict as a Hasid.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in his ideas and, and in his, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I would say, his interests, he was not really a Hasid.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Of course, he was very strict and very stiff-necked and above all, extremely principled.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
